                <updated>Wed, 31 Dec 2014 16:29:39 +0000</updated>
                            <resolved>Tue, 13 Dec 2011 15:31:03 +0000</resolved>
                                    <version>Nightly Builds</version>
                                    <fixVersion>2.0</fixVersion>
                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>0</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13168437" author="markt" created="Tue, 13 Dec 2011 15:31:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I made the method synchronized to align it with GKOP.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13168489" author="samira-t" created="Tue, 13 Dec 2011 16:36:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This bug was detected using &lt;a href=&quot;http://keshmesh.cs.illinois.edu&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Keshmesh &lt;/a&gt; which is a static tool for finding concurrency bug pattern. &lt;a href=&quot;http://keshmesh.cs.illinois.edu/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Keshmesh&lt;/a&gt; reported the accesses to &lt;tt&gt;org.apache.commons.pool2.impl.GenericObjectPool.evictor&lt;/tt&gt; as instances of a generalized form of the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.securecoding.cert.org/confluence/display/java/VNA00-J.+Ensure+visibility+when+accessing+shared+primitive+variables&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;VNA00-J&lt;/a&gt; bug pattern. We used &lt;tt&gt;org.apache.commons.pool2.impl.GenericObjectPool.startEvictor(long)&lt;/tt&gt; as entry point.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
